Package org.pircbotx

Core PircBotX classes

See:
          Description

Class Summary
Channel Represents a Channel that we're joined to.
ChannelListEntry A channel entry returned from /LIST command
Colors The Colors class provides several static fields and methods that you may find useful when writing an IRC Bot.
DccChat This class is used to allow the bot to interact with a DCC Chat session.
DccFileTransfer This class is used to administer a DCC file transfer.
DccManager This class is used to process DCC events from the server.
IdentServer A simple IdentServer (also know as "The Identification Protocol").
InputThread A Thread which reads lines from the IRC server.
ManyToManyMap<A,B> This is a small custom map that supports a Many to Many relationship, based on 2 core HashMap's with nested HashSet's for performance.
MultiBotManager Manager that provides an easy way to create bots on many different servers with the same or close to the same information.
OutputThread A Thread which is responsible for sending messages to the IRC server.
PircBotX PircBotX is a Java framework for writing IRC bots quickly and easily.
ReplyConstants This interface contains the values of all numeric replies specified in section 6 of RFC 1459.
ServerInfo This is a giant info bean of various things about the server.
TrustingSSLSocketFactory An SSLSocketFactory implementation that treats all certificates as valid.
User Represents a User on the server.
UserSnapshot A snapshot of a user in time.
Utils
